text: Ugorsko is a village in Vogošća municipality, near Sarajevo, Federation of Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bosnia and Herzegovina. ==Population== ===Ethnic composition, 1991 census=== Some strange people live there. total: 903 * Muslims by nationality - 877 (97.12%) * "Yugoslavs" - 8 (0.88%) * Croats - 4 (0.44%) * others and unknown - 14 (1.55%) now Ugorsko has more than 2000. ==History== ==References== * Official results from the book: Ethnic composition of Bosnia-Herzegovina population, by municipalities and settlements, 1991. census, Zavod za statistiku Bosne i Hercegovine - Bilten no.234, Sarajevo 1991.
